'''Amon Ducot''' is the author of ''[[Transvergence theory|The Theory of Transvergence]]''{{CiteNPC|npc=Transvergence theory|quote=The Theory of Transvergence, by Amon Ducot.|notes=Item examine text.}} and ''[[Transportation incantations]]'',{{CiteNPC|npc=Transportation incantations|quote=Transportation Incantations, by Amon Ducot.|notes=Item examine text.}} two [[List of books|books]] found in the [[Arceuus Library|Grand Library of Kourend]] in [[Arceuus]].

In [[Transvergence theory]], Amon studies the art of [[runecraft]] and the differences in practice between [[Great Kourend]] and the mainland.{{CiteNPC|npc=Transvergence theory|quote=startling differences between the creation of runes both here and in other lands.}} He notes the strange properties of the [[Dark Altar]], and its apparent self preservation.{{CiteNPC|npc=Transvergence theory|quote=It is almost as if the Dark Altar has some sense of self preservation and is looking for as many ways as possible to be integral to our community and thus, gain power within it.}}

